      <h2>Talks and Presentations</h2>

        <p>Over more than 35 years as an industry scientist, educator, and academic, <a href="/about-dr-lavian/">Dr. Tal Lavian</a> has co-authored and presented at leading conferences and scientific workshops worldwide. The presentation slides are available for download below.</p>

        <p>As an expert in <a href="/communications-expert-witness/network-communications-expert-witness/">network communications</a>, Dr. Lavian has presented on essential innovations spanning <a href="/communications-expert-witness/telecommunications-expert-witness/">telecommunications</a>, data communications, network architecture, broadband, Internet protocols, VoIP, and video streaming. His research is <a href="/scientific-publications/">widely cited</a> within the technology industry and academia.</p>

        <h2>Presentations in the areas of:</h2>

        <ul>
          <li>Network protocols and software applications&mdash;including the data link, network, and transport layers (L2, L3, L4) plus data center network architecture</li>
          <li>LANs, WANs, VPNs, and routing protocols&mdash;from RIP, BGP, MPLS, and OSPF to multicast, DNS, QoS, switching, and packet switching</li>
          <li>PSTN as well as IP telephony, VoIP, SIP, RTP, SS7</li>
          <li>Streaming media, SMS and instant messaging/chat via video and audio</li>
          <li>Wi-Fi and 802.11 Standards</li>
          <li>Wireless LAN (WLAN)</li>
          <li>TCP/IP Suite, TCP, UDP, and IP</li>
          <li>Ethernet and IEEE 802.3 Standard</li>
          <li>IETF RFC standards</li>
        </ul>

